I‚Äôve been using Nix / NixOS for a couple years now, but have never really bothered to learn the NixOS testing framework. After playing with it a bit, I really like it!
It‚Äôs like all the best properties of classic Vagrant and Chef Test Kitchen, but with the power and reproducibility of Nix.

[Andreas Fuchs‚Äô blogged](https://boinkor.net/2024/02/saved-by-nixos-integration-tests-surprisingly/) about how NixOS tests actually helped them catch a regression in their code, so I felt inspired to give it a try.

Since I use nix flakes for all my personal development and machine setup, and the [Nix documentation](https://nixos.org/manual/nixos/stable/index.html#sec-nixos-tests) doesn‚Äôt go into detail about
how to use the NixOS test harness with flakes, I wrote up my initial investigation here.

This setup will allow us to:

1. Build a custom package with nix flakes.
1. Run that package as a NixOS systemd service via a NixOS module.
1. Boot a QEMU machine and execute automated tests against the package / module configuration.

Because it‚Äôs Nix, the entire process of building the package, assembling it into a systemd service, booting a QEMU VM, and executing tests all happens
with a single command with a declarative build definition.

First, setup a bare-bones flake with a custom package. For this example, we‚Äôll just make a simple `netcat` echo server that listens on port 3000.

**flake.nix**

```nix
{
  description = "NixOS tests example";

  inputs = {
    nixpkgs.url = "github:nixos/nixpkgs/nixos-23.11";
    flake-utils.url = "github:numtide/flake-utils";
  };

  outputs = { self, nixpkgs, flake-utils }:
    flake-utils.lib.eachDefaultSystem (system:
      let
        pkgs = nixpkgs.legacyPackages.${system};
      in
        {
          packages = {
            helloNixosTests = pkgs.writeScriptBin "hello-nixos-tests" ''
            ${pkgs.netcat}/bin/nc -l 3000
            '';
          };
        }
    );
}
``` Once you save your `flake.nix` file, you should be able to build the package from within the directory:

```
$ nix build '.#helloNixosTests'
$ ./result/bin/hello-nixos-tests
```

